==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] [[obligare]] ''[[obligate]]'', from [[ob-]] ''to'' + [[ligare]] ''to bind'', from [[PIE]] [[*leig-]] ''to bind''.

===Pronunciation===
/α'bligətəri, -tri/,

===Adjective===
'''obligatory''' 
#imposing obligation, morally or legally; [[binding]]: an [[obligatory]] promise. 
#requiring a matter or [[obligation]]. 

